We engage suppliers 
globally to align our expectations for 
respecting human rights;

Our comprehensive approach to 
reducing and avoiding carbon emissions focuses on key 
sectors of our business, including delivery and logistics;

Embodied emissions in the buildings sector are generated 
from the manufacture, transportation, installation, 
maintenance, and disposal of building materials.

Achieving this ambitious goal will require a 
multifaceted approach that spans Amazon’s delivery and 
logistics networks;

reviewing wage policies, 
including clarification that illegal wage deductions are 
prohibited;

providing additional training to vendors 
in the region on how to implement our Supply Chain 
Standards, including responsible recruitment practices;

Four pillars anchor this work: 
Science, Technology, Engineering, Arts, and Math 
(STEAM) Education;

an AWS Generative AI 
Scholarship that provides high school and university students 
with access to a new generative AI course on Udacity;
